# Chief of Staff — machine-local secrets.  TEMPLATE.
#
# Copy this to `config/secrets.env` (gitignored) and fill in the real value:
#     cp config/secrets.env.example config/secrets.env
#     $EDITOR config/secrets.env
#
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY is the only LLM / billed secret here. The vault MCP bridge (:8005) is the
# only bridge that makes OUTBOUND LLM calls — it embeds the Claude Agent SDK and runs a headless
# session per tool call — so it needs a real Anthropic API key. Every other bridge talks only to
# localhost and makes NO LLM calls. The one other entry below — FITNESS_PUSH_TOKEN — is not an
# external credential at all but a machine-local shared secret the fitness bridge uses to
# authenticate its writes to the board (no billing, no external service).
#
# The vault bridge's launch wrapper (mcp/vault-server/launch.sh, invoked by the launchd
# plist) sources THIS file at startup and exports the key into the server's environment, so
# the secret lives in exactly one machine-local file — never in the installed plist, never
# committed.  Rotate by editing this file and restarting the bridge:
#     launchctl kickstart -k gui/$(id -u)/com.chiefofstaff.mcp-vault
#
# Get a key at https://console.anthropic.com → Settings → API keys → Create Key.
# NOTE: this is billed API usage (separate from any Claude subscription) — each vault tool
# call is a full model session and costs tokens.
#
# Used SOLELY by the vault MCP (mcp/vault-server) — the one component that runs LLM calls
# (it embeds the Claude Agent SDK and is itself an agent). Every other component is a
# deterministic state machine that NEVER calls an LLM, so NO other component reads this key.
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx

# Fitness add-on (mcp/fitness-server) — machine-local shared secret, OPTIONAL.
#
# The fitness bridge attaches this as the `x-fitness-token` header on its WRITE tools so the
# board's token-gated routes (POST /api/fitness/push, /api/fitness/coaching) accept Apple-Watch
# pushes + agent-generated coaching artifacts. It is NOT an external/LLM credential and is NOT
# billed — it just gates writes to your own localhost board. Set the SAME value here and in the
# board's environment, then restart the bridge:
#     launchctl kickstart -k gui/$(id -u)/com.chiefofstaff.mcp-fitness
#
# Leave it unset to run the fitness add-on read-only (the READ tools still work; WRITE tools
# return a clean "FITNESS_PUSH_TOKEN is not configured" error). The fitness bridge's launch
# wrapper (mcp/fitness-server/launch.sh) sources THIS file, so the token never lands in the
# installed plist, in .mcp.json, or in any committed file. Read by mcp/fitness-server ONLY.
FITNESS_PUSH_TOKEN=